        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(feishu): route SDK HTTP through ambient proxy",
        "body": "AI-assisted contribution.\n\n## Summary\n\n- Route Feishu/Lark SDK HTTP requests through OpenClaw's ambient proxy agent and set `proxy: false` so axios does not take a separate HTTPS proxy path.\n- Reuse the same proxy-aware HTTP instance for `WSClient` bootstrap requests while preserving WebSocket heartbeat config and callbacks.\n- Preserve request-level `httpAgent`/`httpsAgent` values for ordinary ambient proxy env, but override them while OpenClaw managed proxy mode is active so Feishu SDK HTTP cannot bypass the operator proxy boundary.\n\nFixes #48949\n\n## Verification\n\n- `pnpm install`\n- `pnpm test extensions/feishu/src/client.test.ts`\n- `pnpm test src/plugin-sdk/extension-shared.test.ts`\n- `pnpm format:check extensions/feishu/src/client.ts extensions/feishu/src/client.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `pnpm test:extension feishu`\n- `pnpm check:changed`\n- `codex review --base origin/main` (twice before the managed-proxy follow-up; no actionable regressions found)\n\n## Real Behavior Proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Feishu token/API and WebSocket bootstrap failed when the gateway process had `HTTP_PROXY`/`HTTPS_PROXY` configured, producing `tenant_access_token` failures and 400 responses containing \"The plain HTTP request was sent to HTTPS port\".\n\nReal environment tested: WSL2 Ubuntu host running OpenClaw 2026.5.22 with the systemd user gateway and `HTTP_PROXY`/`HTTPS_PROXY`/`OPENCLAW_PROXY_URL=http://127.0.0.1:7890`. To avoid replacing this source checkout into my live gateway, I first applied the equivalent dist hotfix to the installed Feishu plugin, restarted the gateway, then ported the same fix to source in this PR.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n\n```console\n$ systemctl --user is-active openclaw-gateway\nactive\n\n$ openclaw channels status --channel feishu --deep --probe\nChecking channel status (probe)...\nGateway reachable.\n- Feishu default: enabled, configured, running, works\n\nTip: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli#status adds gateway health probes to status output (requires a reachable gateway).\n\n$ journalctl --user -u openclaw-gateway --since '2026-05-25 15:12:04' --no-pager | rg 'Request failed with status code 400|connect failed|unable to connect|socket hang up|tenant_access_token|bot identity|ws client ready|bot open_id resolved'\nMay 25 15:12:04 jamietop node[13765]: 2026-05-25T15:12:04.501+08:00 [feishu] feishu[default]: bot open_id resolved: ou_[redacted]\nMay 25 15:12:04 jamietop node[13765]: 2026-05-25T15:12:04.945+08:00 [info]: [ '[ws]', 'ws client ready' ]\n```\n\nEvidence after fix: The probe reported `Feishu default: enabled, configured, running, works`; gateway logs showed `bot open_id resolved` and `[ws] ws client ready`. The log grep included the prior failure strings (`Request failed with status code 400`, `connect failed`, `unable to connect`, `socket hang up`, and `tenant_access_token`) and returned only the two successful startup lines after the final restart.\n\nObserved result after fix: Feishu API probing and WebSocket startup both recovered in the proxy-enabled environment.\n\nWhat was not tested: I did not swap this source checkout into the live gateway or run the repository-wide `pnpm build && pnpm check && pnpm test`; this PR includes targeted source tests, `test:extension feishu`, `check:changed`, managed-proxy agent override unit coverage, and live validation through the equivalent installed-package hotfix.\n",
        "branch": "fix-feishu-proxy-http-instance",
